      • uploadToCMSUsingFileToFolderPath

        public static org.apache.chemistry.opencmis.client.api.Document uploadToCMSUsingFileToFolderPath(java.lang.String parentFolderPath,
                                                                                 java.lang.String fileName,
                                                                                 java.lang.String fileType,
                                                                                 java.io.File file)
                                                                                          throws java.lang.Exception
        Uploads a file to a folder in CMS; The newly created document node in CMS will have specific given filename and not the name of file which is uploaded; and with specified fileType; This method can be useful when the file-types are new or unknown in which case java.nio.file.Files call won't be able to probe the contenttype of a given file

        parentFolderPath - - parent folder path in CMS
        fileName - - filename to be used in CMS document node creation
        fileType - - Content Type / MimeType of file being uploaded
        file - - file to be uploaded
        Returns:
        - returns a newly created document node in CMS repository
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - - Throws exception if it fails to upload the file-contents to CMS repository

      • sanitizeFileFolderNames

        public static java.lang.String sanitizeFileFolderNames(java.lang.String input)
        As there are certain characters which are not allowed in alfresco as file and folder names, we need to replace those charasters with "_" chars < (less than), > (greater than), : (colon), " (double quote), / (forward slash), \ (backslash), | (vertical bar or pipe), ? (question mark), * (asterisk)
        Returns:
        sanitized string after replacing the invalid chars with all "_", and trimming its length to 254
